criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Men or women aged 18-99 years old;

          -  Inpatients who had been diagnosed with type 2 diabetes;

          -  Subjects who are on treatment with insulin for at least 3 months;

          -  HbA1c: 7.0%-10.0%.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients who were diagnosed with T1D, gestational diabetes or other specific types of
             diabetes.

          -  Subjects with acute complications of diabetes such as ketoacidosis or hyperglycemic
             hyperosmolar state;

          -  Patients with severe cardiac, hepatic, renal or general diseases;

          -  Subjects that are, in the judgement of the investigator, unlikely to comply with the
             protocol.

          -  Absence of informed consent.
